cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with cryptographic protocols and the design of functions for use in those protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC), as it discusses the relationship between P and NP. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) in its discussion of invertibility and noninvertibility of functions.
